Random distribution policy is Great because many scenarios do not need query very fast, but need load data to the system stable and fast.
If the table is created using random distribution policy, it is better to write to a single tablet during load process. It will reduce the number of versions in BE, will reduce compaction and improve load stability.
For example, clickhouse prefers to load a single local table to a distributed table.
